      "raw_text": "The feeling is growing among\nsome members of the city council\nTHAT 1t might be well to modify the\nstreet speaking ordinance. If the\nmayor should recommend a modi-\nfication 50 as to leave it discretion\nAIRY with himself and the police as\nto when street speaking should be\npermitted, it is probable that the\ncouncil would make the amend\nment.\n\n\nWhen a like situation came up\nIn Seattle over year ago under\nex-Moyar Moore there were numer-\nGUS clashes and considerable hard\nfeeling. The mayor, Mr.. Taylor,\nspeedily settled the matter by let\nting the soap box\" orators go\nahead and spiel. SO long as they\nheld themselves within the law as\nto incendiary utterances or incit-\nIng to riot. Seattle has no further\ntrouble of this kind at the present."
    }
